1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,420
 (soft music)

2
00:00:02,420 --> 00:00:18,180
 Well, in my line of work,

3
00:00:18,180 --> 00:00:21,540
 I often find myself giving the same advice

4
00:00:21,540 --> 00:00:24,580
 to people all the time.

5
00:00:24,580 --> 00:00:29,360
 It's not because their situations aren't unique

6
00:00:29,360 --> 00:00:30,880
 or their circumstances aren't challenging

7
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:34,880
 or their problems are particularly difficult.

8
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:41,000
 Really what it is, is I give advice to young adults a lot

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,480
 and young adults are often going

10
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:45,760
 through the same set of circumstances as one another.

11
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:47,480
 We find that you're going through

12
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:49,400
 many of the same life events,

13
00:00:49,400 --> 00:00:52,400
 facing many of the same challenges as one another.

14
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:55,920
 And so I'm constantly repeating the same things to people.

15
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,200
 So I thought I would just stand up here

16
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,740
 and I would just tell you what I might tell you

17
00:00:58,740 --> 00:01:00,880
 if you ever came up to me.

18
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:02,600
 So you can identify for yourself

19
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:04,000
 if you fall into one of these categories,

20
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:07,040
 but maybe you're here and you're anxious about the future.

21
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:09,800
 What I would tell you is you can't predict

22
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:11,440
 what will happen tomorrow,

23
00:01:11,440 --> 00:01:14,120
 but you can prepare what's happening today.

24
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:16,920
 Maybe you're frustrated with God.

25
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:19,920
 I would tell you just because God is silent

26
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:22,280
 doesn't mean that God is absent.

27
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:25,280
 Maybe you're here and you're reconciling with someone.

28
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:28,060
 I would tell you forgiveness is given in a moment.

29
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:32,720
 But trust, trust is earned over time.

30
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:35,280
 Maybe you're unfulfilled at work.

31
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,160
 Show of hands, anybody?

32
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:37,560
 Just kidding, don't do that.

33
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:41,400
 I would tell you money is a useful tool,

34
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,840
 but it makes a terrible master.

35
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:46,560
 Maybe you're struggling with sin.

36
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:50,040
 I would tell you nothing likes to die,

37
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:53,680
 but certainly some things should.

38
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:56,560
 Maybe you feel misunderstood.

39
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:59,040
 And I would tell you, hey, you can have the best

40
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:01,640
 of intentions and still be wrong.

41
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:04,720
 Some of you need to learn discipline.

42
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:08,800
 I would tell you small habits,

43
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:11,520
 they matter more than big decisions.

44
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,980
 Some of you, you're here tonight

45
00:02:12,980 --> 00:02:14,800
 and you feel spiritually stuck.

46
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:17,720
 And I would tell you growth rarely happens

47
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:18,940
 in your comfort zone.

48
00:02:18,940 --> 00:02:22,260
 So you should try getting out of it.

49
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:23,880
 Some of you, you can't find community.

50
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:26,000
 And so I would tell you, you should be the kind of friend

51
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,080
 that you want to find.

52
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:30,060
 Others of you, you're on the verge of burnout.

53
00:02:30,060 --> 00:02:34,720
 And I would say, rest isn't laziness, it's obedience.

54
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:36,320
 And I heard from all the people, amen,

55
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:37,900
 'cause everybody wants some of that.

56
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:40,160
 But of all the advice that I give,

57
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:42,880
 there is one piece of advice that I give

58
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:46,100
 more than any other piece of advice.

59
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:49,320
 And it is always to those that are lost in love.

60
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:50,960
 And it's this piece of advice.

61
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:52,840
 Just because they're into you

62
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:56,020
 does not mean they're good for you.

63
00:02:56,020 --> 00:02:59,120
 And it doesn't matter how many times I say it.

64
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,840
 And it doesn't matter how many kinds of reactions

65
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:01,960
 I get like that.

66
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:04,400
 People inevitably fall for someone

67
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,880
 because they have all the charisma in the world,

68
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:09,480
 but they don't have any of the character to match.

69
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,560
 You know what I'm talking about?

70
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:13,720
 Like you know the guy that he looks as good in person

71
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:15,160
 as he does online.

72
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:17,500
 He actually has good hygiene.

73
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:20,800
 He actually has gone through his scent journey.

74
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,600
 He is actually driven in life

75
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,160
 and he gives you good reason to go home

76
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,400
 and talk to all the roommates

77
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,160
 until the wee hours of the morning.

78
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:30,680
 That is until he starts lacking effort

79
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:33,840
 and he starts leaving you wondering,

80
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:36,600
 what the heck was I ever thinking to begin with?

81
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:37,480
 You know this.

82
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:39,040
 You know that you often might find yourself

83
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:40,080
 valuing charisma over character.

84
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:42,360
 Gentlemen, the number of times I have visited with you

85
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:45,680
 and you have projected on some young lady

86
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:47,680
 that she is so godly.

87
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:51,120
 She has a high spirituality and devotion to Jesus.

88
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,200
 When in reality, she doesn't.

89
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,720
 You just can't believe the fact

90
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:56,600
 that someone that attractive is actually into you.

91
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:57,840
 The truth of the matter is,

92
00:03:57,840 --> 00:04:00,840
 we often find ourselves listening to good advice,

93
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,360
 but not heeding really good advice.

94
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:05,160
 This happens all the time.

95
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:07,680
 Like no matter how good the advice is that's offered,

96
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:12,680
 some lessons, you just gotta learn the hard way.

97
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:15,300
 Now, why do I tell you that?

98
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:18,680
 Because the same is true in every area of life.

99
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:21,900
 Like despite good advice and reliable insights

100
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:23,360
 and available truth,

101
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:26,920
 every one of us has chosen to learn something the hard way.

102
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:29,440
 Like for some of you, you didn't believe your parents

103
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:31,760
 when they told you to stop applying for credit cards.

104
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:33,600
 And so you had to ruin your credit

105
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:37,360
 to realize my parents were actually right.

106
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,480
 Others of you,

107
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:41,800
 you refuse to get your vehicle registration updated.

108
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,520
 That is until you get pulled over

109
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:46,620
 and that officer actually fines you for it.

110
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:51,620
 Some of you, you have waited to get your taxes done

111
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,360
 and it's gonna take someone like me

112
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,720
 standing on a stage like this,

113
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:57,760
 looking at you and telling you they're due tomorrow.

114
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,680
 And you're gonna feel the ensuing panic

115
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:02,840
 that pushes you into the wee hours of this morning,

116
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:05,580
 trying to make sure that you get those taxes done.

117
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:08,240
 Like against all judgment, we do this.

118
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,080
 Why?

119
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:11,160
 Why do we do this to ourself?

120
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:13,040
 Like there's not an exception in the room.

121
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:15,920
 Every one of us is liable to this kind of thing.

122
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:16,880
 So why?

123
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,300
 Like, why do we do this?

124
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:20,640
 Why do we choose to learn things the hard way?

125
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:21,840
 Here's what I would say.

126
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:23,400
 I would tell you the reason you choose

127
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:24,440
 to learn things the hard way

128
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:28,240
 is because people do not change by way of an explanation.

129
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:30,480
 They change by way of an experience.

130
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:33,640
 People change by way of an experience.

131
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:35,140
 Like even though someone else's experience

132
00:05:35,140 --> 00:05:36,100
 is often the best teacher,

133
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,760
 which is why you should listen to someone else's advice.

134
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:40,040
 You don't want to trust their experience.

135
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,720
 You would rather learn it for yourself

136
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,800
 and live it on your own

137
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:47,320
 and reap the pain that may come through the process.

138
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:50,360
 And God knows that we're hardwired this way.

139
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,660
 And I love him for it

140
00:05:51,660 --> 00:05:54,680
 because God doesn't come to a single one of us.

141
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:57,240
 He doesn't come to anyone

142
00:05:57,240 --> 00:06:00,040
 and expect them to believe in him

143
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:02,560
 by way of explanation alone.

144
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:05,240
 He expects people to believe in him

145
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:08,320
 by way of a personal experience.

146
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:10,900
 He wants people to encounter him.

147
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:16,120
 And that's what we're gonna see happens to the story

148
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,800
 in the man that we're looking at tonight.

149
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,640
 So if you've got a Bible,

150
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:20,920
 turn with me to Genesis chapter 28.

151
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,600
 While you're turning there,

152
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:25,200
 tonight we're catching up with a character

153
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,520
 that some of you may be familiar with

154
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,560
 in the book of Genesis named Jacob.

155
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,760
 If you're not familiar,

156
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,840
 Jacob is one of the patriarchs in the Bible.

157
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,580
 He's one of the most important characters

158
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:34,420
 in the book of Genesis.

159
00:06:34,420 --> 00:06:36,280
 He is the son of Isaac.

160
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:38,360
 He is the grandson of Abraham.

161
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:41,280
 He is the father of 12 different sons,

162
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:45,240
 all of whom ultimately represent the 12 tribes of Israel.

163
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,480
 And to top it off,

164
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:48,600
 he's the namesake of the people of Israel himself.

165
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,080
 If you read through the life of Jacob,

166
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,600
 you'll get to chapter 22 in Genesis,

167
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,880
 and you'll see that he wrestles things out with God,

168
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,160
 which was a story I really wanted to teach to you,

169
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:58,120
 but I've already taught it to you several years ago.

170
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,580
 So if you're interested in that story, you can go,

171
00:06:59,580 --> 00:07:00,760
 you can find it on our website.

172
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:03,360
 But the point being there is he wrestles with God

173
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:06,040
 and God ultimately bestows upon him a new name.

174
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:08,360
 He tells him, no longer will you be called Jacob.

175
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:10,320
 Your name will now be Yisrael.

176
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:11,800
 You will be Israel.

177
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:16,100
 He literally becomes the namesake of the people of God.

178
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:18,380
 Like he's kind of a big deal.

179
00:07:18,380 --> 00:07:20,200
 And he's kind of a scoundrel.

180
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,360
 Like you see, whenever we're introduced to Jacob

181
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,520
 in Genesis 25,

182
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:27,060
 what we learn is that his name is Jacob or Yaakov in Hebrew.

183
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:32,060
 And that name means heel grabber or a usurper, supplanter.

184
00:07:32,060 --> 00:07:38,200
 And what we realize is he really lives up to that name.

185
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:41,980
 Like he is a con artist of a human being.

186
00:07:41,980 --> 00:07:44,880
 He's not an honest working kind of man.

187
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:46,800
 And yet it is that kind of man

188
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,360
 that God comes to interact with tonight.

189
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:54,360
 He comes to lead Jacob into a relationship with him.

190
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,240
 Not on the basis of explanation,

191
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,600
 but on the basis of experience.

192
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,440
 So here's what we see.

193
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:00,680
 We read it.

194
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:04,200
 As we jump into verse 10,

195
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,500
 we see it says this.

196
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:12,360
 Jacob, a man that had never been enough in life.

197
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:14,640
 A man that he never measured up to his brother.

198
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,240
 He never impressed his father.

199
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,960
 He never lived up to his family name.

200
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:22,960
 That man, he left Beersheba, he went toward Haran.

201
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:25,360
 We gotta stop and we gotta talk about why he's doing that.

202
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:27,800
 Why is he leaving Beersheba and going to Haran?

203
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:28,760
 He's going there

204
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:31,580
 because he is literally running for his life.

205
00:08:31,580 --> 00:08:35,840
 Like so devious, so deceitful is Jacob

206
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:38,040
 that between chapter 25 and chapter 28,

207
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:41,240
 we learn that he has swindled his brother Esau

208
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,480
 out of his birthright.

209
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:46,720
 He has deceived his father out of his blessing

210
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:49,720
 and he has brought shame upon his name.

211
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:52,280
 And so he literally, he runs for the hills

212
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:55,600
 because Esau is trying to track him down and take his life.

213
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:59,480
 So he is running to Haran and he came to a certain place

214
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:04,120
 and he stayed there that night because the sun had set.

215
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:06,440
 Taking one of the stones of the place,

216
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:08,360
 he put it under his head as people do

217
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:10,600
 and he laid down in that place to sleep.

218
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,840
 You see it?

219
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:14,400
 For all intents and purposes, Jacob is in a moment

220
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:17,520
 many of us can relate to ourselves.

221
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:19,880
 Not necessarily the stone as a pillow sort of thing,

222
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:22,080
 but he has left his hometown.

223
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,880
 He has come to a new city.

224
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,980
 He's running from his past

225
00:09:26,980 --> 00:09:30,040
 and all the guilt that haunts him back there.

226
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:32,540
 He has arrived into the present

227
00:09:32,540 --> 00:09:36,680
 and yet he's confused about how he has ended up

228
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,220
 as he is and who he is.

229
00:09:38,220 --> 00:09:40,140
 And he's anxious about the future.

230
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:42,520
 He's uncertain about the days ahead.

231
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:44,480
 Like despite all the scheming and the angling

232
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:45,880
 and the finessing and the deceiving

233
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,000
 to get where he's always wanted to be,

234
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,540
 what we learn is that Jacob's self-reliance

235
00:09:49,540 --> 00:09:54,540
 has only gotten him here, rock bottom, straight out of luck.

236
00:09:54,540 --> 00:10:00,280
 And it's then that God comes to him.

237
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:02,520
 We see it in verse 12.

238
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:05,640
 "And he dreamed, and behold,

239
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:08,760
 there was a ladder set upon the earth.

240
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:11,240
 And the top of it reached to heaven.

241
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:13,240
 And behold, the angels of God,

242
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,400
 they were ascending and descending on it.

243
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:17,940
 And behold, the Lord stood above it."

244
00:10:17,940 --> 00:10:21,400
 Now stop right there because this is very important.

245
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:25,560
 God comes to us when we least expect it.

246
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:28,360
 He comes to us when we least expect it.

247
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:29,880
 Like God doesn't come to Jacob

248
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:32,040
 in the middle of some spiritual pilgrimage.

249
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:34,240
 He doesn't come to Jacob after fasting

250
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:37,120
 and praying for weeks on end to arrive in this moment.

251
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:39,160
 He does not come to Jacob after he has offered

252
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:41,480
 some sort of grand sacrifice and surrender.

253
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,920
 He comes to Jacob when?

254
00:10:42,920 --> 00:10:45,440
 He comes to Jacob when he's asleep,

255
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:47,520
 which he might do for some of you every week.

256
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,920
 I see a couple of you guys that are dozing off.

257
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:51,260
 And I'm like, man, this might be the night

258
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:53,140
 that God encounters them very powerfully

259
00:10:53,140 --> 00:10:55,360
 because he did it then, he could do it again.

260
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:57,080
 He comes to him when he's asleep.

261
00:10:57,080 --> 00:11:02,080
 He comes to him when he is least expecting it.

262
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:04,520
 So when I was a junior in college,

263
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:06,920
 I had a couple of friends that really wanted to apply

264
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:09,500
 for this business organization.

265
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:11,880
 And yet I thought it was a really dumb idea.

